      "SummaryText": "to train personnel for emergency response in the event of a release, including maintaining a trained onsite fire brigade.  To date, no accidents with offsite impacts have occurred at these facilities.\r\nIn addition to the above Clean Air Act requirements, Asarco is in compliance with the OSHA PSM, EPA SPCC, OSHA HAZWOPER, EPCRA, and EPA RCRA Contingency Planning requirements.  Asarco has also conducted a process hazard analysis on the SO2 process, the only PSM-covered process at ACR. \r\n\r\nAsarco has one program level 2 process involving HCl and two program level 3 processes involving SO2.  Asarco's original (June 14, 1999) RMP submittal to EPA included two program level 2 processes involving HCl, and one process involving propane at program level 1.  One of the two HCl processes no longer exists since Asarco no longer receives and stores HCl in railcars.  Instead HCl is delivered by tanker truck and is unloaded immediately into the HCl storage tanks.  Additionally, the propane process is no longer covered under the RMP rule since propane used as a fuel source has been exempted under the Chemical Safety Information, Site Security and Fuels Regulatory Relief Act (Pub. L. 106-40).  \r\n\r\nAsarco has implemented safety precautions and procedures designed to prevent and mitigate catastrophic releases.  Asarco has active operating, maintenance, training, and inspection procedures; a trained fire brigade; and an evacuation plan for each area.  In addition, Asarco has coordinated emergency response with the LEPC.\r\n\r\nAsarco's management is committed to the following:\r\n-\tPreventing accidents;\r\n-\tTraining our employees in correct response procedures in the event of an accident;\r\n-\tParticipating in community emergency preparedness;\r\n-\tAddressing any citizen concerns by fully explaining potential hazards associated with Asarco operations and all steps being taken to prevent and mitigate accidents; and\r\n-\tBeing a good corporate citizen of Potter County.\r\n\tWith these objectives in mind"
